Corporate & Institutional Banking
BNP Paribas, Tokyo Branch
BNP Paribas Securities (Japan) Limited
Asset Management
Insurance

 





Asset Management

Forward to a friendForward to a friend
PrintPrint
 

BNP Paribas Asset Management is the dedicated, autonomous asset management business of BNP Paribas Group and offers the full range of asset management services to both institutional and retail clients around the world.
As a global investment solutions provider, our fund offering spans across traditional asset classes (equity, fixed income) to more complex ones (alternative investment, structured products) as well as transverse investment themes (SRI, emerging markets). Through our worldwide presence and our partnerships with renowned asset managers, we offer a full range of expertise in all those fields.
A client-centric organisation, BNP Paribas Asset Management is structured around three business lines: institutional, distribution and Asia Pacific & emerging markets. We have some 700 investment professionals globally, each specialising in a particular asset class or product type.
Since its establishment in 1998, BNP Paribas Investment Partners Japan Ltd. has developed comprehensive asset management service primarily to institutional investors and individual investors through distributors. Backed by the resource and credibility of the BNP Paribas Group, we offer the best investment solutions and with services that are tailored to their specific needs to our clietns in Japan.

Corporate information:
CEO and Representative Director: Ryohei Shimazaki
Kanto Local Financial Bureau Registration No.378
Member of The Investment Trust Association Japan, and Type II Financial Instruments Firms Association



BNP Paribas Asset Management
https://www.bnpparibas-am.com/en/




BNP Paribas Investment Partners in Japan - in Japanese
www.bnpparibas-am.jp






















