Investment Strategies 
							 
																	View all																




We manage a broad range of strategies for institutional clients, spanning equities, fixed income and multi-asset solutions



Our Experts


 

Colin Graham
Head of Active Asset Allocation
Colin Graham, CFA, CAIA, is the Chief Investment Officer and Head of Active Asset Allocation for the Multi Asset Solutions team at BNP Paribas Asset Management. He is responsible for our active asset allocation views and leads the team’s strategists, economists and analysts. Colin joined our company in 2014 and is based in London. Prior to joining us, Colin was Co-Head of Global Multi Asset Strategies at BlackRock and Actuarial Consultant for Mercer. Colin has 25 years of investment experience. He holds a BSc in Management and Mathematics from Brunel University in the UK. He is a CFA Charterholder and a Chartered Alternative Investment Analyst.





Asset allocation update - 5 July - Colin Graham 
Hear from Colin Graham
Head of Active Asset Allocation






About us



We provide institutional investors with high-quality investment products and services focusing on global and regional multi-asset, equity and fixed income strategies.



